parameters:
Sage Amakane: "First, we must gather the orbs. I'm counting on both of
you."

Sage Amakane: "I'm concerned about Lize's curse as well... But what
could it mean that the Void, said to reduce everything to nothingness,
has spawned the three generals of darkness? What exactly is the Void?"
Sage Amakane: "Both of you... please take good care of the jewel."

Sage Amakane: "There's a horde of undead, but as long as we have the
barrier, it shouldn't be a problem. What concerns me is that horned
girl..."
Sage Amakane: "Both of you... please take good care of the jewel."

Sage Amakane: "The tower's barrier won't be broken easily. What
concerns me is that horned girl, though..."

Sage Amakane: "It seems we don't have much time left. I'm counting on
both of you..."

Sage Amakane: "Flora, please take good care of Lize. I'm sure you
can..."
Amakane has a slightly sad expression on her face.

Sage Amakane: "You both have truly worked hard. Please take some time
to rest your bodies."
Amakane is gazing at the two with a full-faced smile.

Sage Amakane: "Flora, Lize, thank you so much for everything. Really,
uuu..."

Amakane blinks her eyes and continues to gaze at the two with a full-
faced smile.

Magician\N[20]: "Come to think of it, they say the Dark Triumvirate
has appeared... Who exactly could they be?"

Magician\N[20]: "My name is \N[20], and it is my duty to serve as a
shield and protect this tower."

Magician\N[19]: "Is that horned girl one of the so-called Three
Generals, I wonder..."

Magician\N[19]: "Leave the tower to me. I shall become a shield and
protect this tower."

Magician\N[20]: "Where could Loretta have disappeared to...? Hmm, it's
concerning."

Magician\N[20]: "I never imagined it would be to that extent... Thank
you for your help."
Magician\N[20]: "With this, our role comes to a temporary close."

Magician\N[20]: "Both of you, it's a relief that you're safe. You've
really done well."

Magician\N[19]: "Gathering the orbs is no easy task. Please be
careful."

Magician\N[19]: "My name is \N[19], and it is my duty to become the
sword that protects this tower."

Magician\N[19] "\N[272], is something happening there? It seems we
can't get in touch."

Magician\N[19] "Please leave the tower to me. I shall protect it with
my sword."

Magician\N[19]: "To be that powerful... The Three Generals of Darkness
are indeed fearsome..."

Magician\N[19]: "To lose so easily... It seems I still have much to
learn."

Magician\N[19]: "Actually, I've been suffering from lack of sleep...
Now I think I'll be able to sleep soundly."
Magician\N[19]: "Thank you, Flora-san. Lize also did a great job."

Sage Amakane: "You must be the Warrior of Light... Thank you for
coming all the way from another world. My name is Amakane, the
caretaker of this tower."
Flora: "I'm Flora. Pleased to meet you."

Sage Amakane: "Ms. Flora... I can feel a very strong power of light
emanating from you. Lize, thank you for your hard work as well."

Sage Amakane: "I believe you've been informed, but this place \N[261]
is the central hub that connects countless other worlds."

Sage Amakane: "If the void causes this world to collapse, your world,
Flora's world, and all other worlds will perish just like \N[261]."

Sage Amakane: "Your mission is to work with Lize to prevent the
calamity known as the void."

The book feels heavy in hand; it's old but somehow fresh, and you can
sense a mysterious power within it.

Sage Amakane: "This is the \N[261] Tome; we call it the Book of
Prophecy."

Sage Amakane: "It was written by a great magician named \N[261], who
is said to have defeated the void long ago and restored light to the
world."

Sage Amakane: "And when the void once again threatened our world, he
left us with instructions on how to counter it."

Sage Amakane: "First, you must obtain the hidden orbs in this land.
Red, green, blue... they are the three orbs of light's primary
colors."

Sage Amakane: "The prophecy states that the first orb lies in the
eastern lands. The exact location is unknown, but I'm sure you, Flora,
will be able to find it."

Can I really do this...? A sudden surge of anxiety tightens my chest
uncomfortably.
Lize: "It's okay. I'm with you... right?"
Lize grips Flora's hand tightly and gives her a reassuring smile.

Flora: "That's right. I think we can manage if you're with me, Lize-
chan."

Sage Amakane: "Then as soon as you're ready, head east to obtain the
first orb. I'm counting on both of you."

Afterwards, the two reported about the curse placed on Lize and their
encounter with one of the three generals of darkness in \N[261]'s
cave, Josephine, before leaving the place.

Flora and her companions talked to Amakane about the orb they had
obtained and what they had heard from Josephine regarding the Demon's
Gate.

Sage Amakane: "Such... The void is a dark vortex. To think that it was
actually the Demon's Gate..."

Sage Amakane: "However... we only have the red orb left to obtain. If
we can secure that, we should be able to manage somehow."

Sage Amakane: "Regarding the remaining orb, reports from our scouts
suggest that the high priest of \N[272] might have some information,
but there's something concerning..."

Sage Amakane: "For some reason, we can't even get in touch with the
high priest, let alone anyone in the town of \N[272]."

Sage Amakane: "Please don't worry about this place, and could you two
head to \N[272] as soon as possible? We must obtain the red orb at all
costs."

Flora and her companions reported to Amakane that they had defeated
the Demon Lord \N[33] and that the dark vortex known as the Void, the
Demon's Gate, had vanished.
Sage Amakane: "Ah, thank goodness. Thank you, Flora-san..."
Sage Amakane: "And Lize, I'm so relieved you're safe too... uuu..."

Sage Amakane: "With this, the role of the Warriors of Light has come
to an end. You've all done very well."

Sage Amakane: "I'll prepare the transfer so that you can return to
your original world whenever you wish from now on."

Sage Amakane: "When the time comes for you to leave this world, please
come to the transfer room inside the tower. Is that alright?"
From now on, you can reach the ending in the transfer room.
